==Strategy==
Much like [[dust devil]]s, greater nechryael in the Catacombs of Kourend are popularly killed using [[Ice Burst]] or [[Ice Barrage]], as players are able to clump them up into a pile and hit them all simultaneously. To do this, turn on [[Protect from Melee]], then attack the nechryael in the chamber they're in with a fast ranged weapon (such as cheap [[dart]]s or [[throwing knife|knives]]) or the special attack of the [[Dinh's bulwark]] to get them aggressive. Run to a side of the room which has two corners adjacent to each other and run back and forth between the two corners so that the nechryael pile on top of each other.

Due to their nonexistent Magic level and defence, the player should prioritise magic-boosting equipment such as a [[kodai wand]] and [[ancestral robes]] over conventional magic armour. If the player does not possess ancestral robes, using [[initiate armour|initiate]] or [[proselyte armour]] is recommended instead for the prayer bonus without sacrificing too much magic accuracy. Runes for blood spells are optional if healing is needed.

When bursting or barraging, it is recommended to pay some attention in case of [[Nechryarch]] spawns, as it is likely that players automatically attack it and its [[chaotic death spawn]]s deal high damage through magic based gear. Some options to deal with it include switching to [[Blood Barrage]] to outheal the damage taken (provided that there are more regular nechryael next to it), using ice spells to safespot it, or running away when the spawns appear to lose their aggression and coming back. 

Greater Nechryael can also be found in a multi-combat setting in the [[Wilderness Slayer Cave]] where they may also be cannoned; however, this is part of the Wilderness and there is the risk of running into player killers. In this location, take less risk and bank more frequently. Fortunately, they are found below level 30 Wilderness so a [[royal seed pod]] can be used for a fast escape option.

Finally, Greater Nechryael also reside in the [[Iorwerth Dungeon]]. Unlike the other two locations, this location is solely single-combat, although a cannon can be permitted in this area. This location requires completion of [[Song of the Elves]] and is ideal for players who are not intending to AoE the nechryaels. 

